\label{cliffordconjecture}
		Let $p : \fQ \to S$ be any quadric fibration of relative dimension $n + 1$ over a smooth base such that the fibers $\fQ_s$ are quadrics of rank at least 4, where $n$ is odd. Then there exists a semiorthogonal decomposition 
		\begin{equation}
			\Db(\OGr(2,\fQ)) = \langle \underbrace{\Db(S,\cl_0), \dots, \Db(S,\cl_0)}_{n+1\text{ times}}, \underbrace{\Db(S), \dots, \Db(S)}_{\frac{(n-1)(n+1)}{2}\text{ times}}\rangle,
		\end{equation}
		where $\Db(S,\cl_0)$ is the derived category of the sheaf of even Clifford algebras over the base $S$ associated to the quadric fibration $\fQ\to S$.

