		The solutions above are smooth in the interior of $\C$, i.e.~for $v<0$.
        Moreover, their scale critical norm on $\{t=-\tau,\abs{r}\leq \tau\}$ remains bounded away from 0 as $\tau\to0$.

        Finally, in all statements, smoothness can be replaced by $C^k$, infinite conormal regularity across $\C$ can be replaced by conormal regularity of degree $k$, and the notation $\mathcal{O}(\dots)$ introduced below \cref{in:conj:type1} can be replaced by $\mathcal{O}_{k}(\dots)$. We then refer to the conjectured solutions as "$k$-regular solutions".

