{8|\beta|^4 (r_{\max}^2 - r_{\min}^2)} - 1,
\; -\frac{1}{2\beta}
\right),
\end{equation}
where $r_{\max}=\max(r_1,r_2)$ and $r_{\min}=\min(r_1,r_2)$,
generates an additional spectral boundary, which may be empty if
Eq.~\eqref{sol1} admits no solution.

\item
When $\dfrac{1}{r_1^2}+\dfrac{1}{r_2^2}\leq 2$, there exists an inner spectral boundary
given by the circle centered at the origin with radius
\begin{equation}
\sqrt{\frac{r_1^2+r_2^2-1-\sqrt{(r_1^2-r_2^2)^2+1}}{2}}.
\end{equation}

\end{itemize}

The conjecture is that these constructions generate all spectral boundaries of $\vb{M}$.

