Let $A, P \in \mathrm{GL}(d, \mathbb{R})$ and $\psi \in L^2 (\mathbb{R}^d)$. Suppose that \[ \{|\det(A)|^{-j/2} \psi (A^j \cdot -  Pk) \}_{j \in \mathbb{Z}, k \in \mathbb{Z}^d}\]
is an orthonormal basis, or more generally a Parseval frame, for $L^2 (\mathbb{R}^d)$. Then the Calder\'on sum formula holds:
\begin{align} \label{eq:calderon}
